window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>This program is read by the author.</b></p> <p><b>\"Adrian Tchaikovsky again proves himself a double threat...the author-narrator brings to life a world that is wasting away.\" —</b><b><i>AudioFile</i></b><b> on </b><b><i>Service Model</i></b></p> <p><b><i>Spiderlight</i></b><b> is an exhilarating fantasy quest from Adrian Tchaikovsky, the author of </b><b><i>Guns at Dawn</i></b><b> and the Shadows of the Apt series.</b></p> <p><i>The path to victory will only be seen through a spider's eyes...</i></p> <p>The Church of Armes of the Light has battled the forces of Darkness for as long as anyone can remember. The great prophecy has foretold that a band of misfits, led by a high priestess will defeat the Dark Lord Darvezian, armed with their wits, the blessing of the Light and an artifact stolen from the merciless Spider Queen.</p> <p>Their journey will be long, hard and fraught with danger. Allies will become enemies; enemies will become allies. And the Dark Lord will be waiting, always waiting…</p> <p><b>A Macmillan Audio production from Tor Books.</b></p>"; 
